[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe program registry is the source of truth for what each program is and who it's for.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This example ships with a small synthetic registry of 5 programs covering disease-specific (heart-failure, diabetes), complex-care, transitional, and polypharmacy archetypes. Production needs structured change management with clinical operations, program leadership, and contracts review, with parallel evaluation against the prior registry version when significant changes ship.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPer-program response (uplift) modeling is the hardest part and the part most teams skip.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Production-grade response estimation requires either randomized enrollment in a fraction of slots or careful causal-inference tooling (propensity matching, doubly-robust estimation, instrumental variables) on observational enrollment data. The training scripts are out of scope for this companion; the main recipe's "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" section walks through the gap. The example uses rule-based proxies.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe engagement-and-retention worker is the part that determines whether enrollment actually translates into outcomes.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This example wires per-program engagement scoring, decline-pattern classification, and retention-strategy dispatch. Production extends with a much richer engagement-event stream, modality-switching automation, and structured retention budgets per cohort.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBedrock model IDs change over time.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some regions require cross-region inference profile IDs (prefixed [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mus.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140meu.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The IDs below are reasonable defaults; verify in the Bedrock console for your region before running.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAll patients, programs, eligibility records, engagement events, and outcome events in the example are synthetic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Do not treat any specific patient_id, program_id, evidence event, enrollment event, or engagement event as real. A production system ingests from real claims, EHR, lab, pharmacy, discharge feeds, and care management system events under BAA.[K
